Unilever shares business update on growth priorities


Unilever highlighted its focus on strengthening core brands, improving operational efficiency, and accelerating innovation across Beauty & Wellbeing, Personal Care, Home Care, and Nutrition. The company reaffirmed its commitment to sustainable sourcing and packaging improvements while driving long-term value for consumers and shareholders.

The company stated that continued investment in brands and simpler operating models remains central to its growth strategy.

fields.title: New Journal Launch: Journal of Applied Physics
fields.excerpt: We are excited to announce the launch of our newest journal, the Journal of Applied Physics, covering cutting-edge research in applied physics and engineering.
fields.content:
Aethra Science Publishers is proud to announce the launch of the Journal of Applied Physics (JAP), a new peer-reviewed publication dedicated to advancing research in applied physics and engineering sciences.

About the Journal

The Journal of Applied Physics aims to publish high-quality original research that bridges fundamental physics with practical applications. The journal covers a broad spectrum of topics including:

  • Condensed matter physics and materials science
  • Optical and photonic technologies
  • Nanotechnology and nanoscience
  • Energy conversion and storage
  • Quantum technologies
  • Computational physics

Editorial Leadership

The journal is led by an internationally recognized editorial board comprising experts from leading research institutions worldwide.

Submit Your Research

We are now accepting submissions. Authors are encouraged to submit their innovative research for consideration. Publication fees are waived for the first year.

fields.title: Strategic Partnership with European Research Council
fields.excerpt: Aethra Science Publishers announces a strategic partnership with the European Research Council to enhance open access publishing for ERC-funded research.
fields.content:
Aethra Science Publishers is pleased to announce a strategic partnership with the European Research Council (ERC) to facilitate open access publishing for ERC-funded researchers.

Partnership Highlights

Under this agreement:

  • ERC grant holders will have streamlined access to open access publishing across all Aethra journals
  • Article processing charges for ERC-funded research will be covered through institutional agreements
  • Enhanced visibility for ERC-funded research through dedicated collections and promotion
  • Compliance with Plan S and other open access mandates will be simplified

Supporting Excellence in Research

This partnership reflects our commitment to supporting excellent research and ensuring that groundbreaking discoveries reach the widest possible audience. The ERC funds frontier research across all fields, and we are honored to help disseminate this important work.

Getting Started

ERC grant holders can contact our institutional partnerships team to learn more about the benefits available under this agreement.

fields.title: Renewable Energy Projects Expand in Rural Areas
fields.excerpt: Several new solar and wind projects were approved to boost clean energy capacity.
fields.content:
Project Details

The developments include small-scale solar farms and community wind installations.

Expected Impact

Officials estimate the projects will supply power to thousands of homes while creating local jobs.

Project Details

The developments include small-scale solar farms and community wind installations designed to integrate with existing local grids. Construction will be phased to reduce disruption and prioritize locally sourced materials. Several projects will be owned or co-managed by regional cooperatives to ensure long-term community participation.

Expected Impact

Officials estimate the projects will supply power to thousands of homes while creating local jobs in construction, maintenance, and operations. Over time, the installations are expected to lower energy costs, reduce carbon emissions, and strengthen energy independence in rural areas.

fields.content:
